This paper is primarily focused on dialog systems and natural language processing, which suggests that it would likely fall under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method of dialog state tracking using a neural network architecture, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a memory-enhanced neural network, which could potentially place it in the category of "Systems and Control" (cs.SY) or "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). However, given the primary focus on dialog systems and natural language processing, it is more likely to fall under cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
